    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-1425

Description:
    Previous versions of the firefox package are vulnerable to several types of
attacks, one of which is understood to potentially allow compromised or
malicious sites to run arbitrary code as the user running the vulnerable
application. A number of cross-site-scripting bugs have also been corrected.

